   357→<!-- WHAT IS IT -->
   358→<section id="what">
   359→  <div class="container">
   360→    <div class="section-label fade-up">What it is</div>
   361→    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">From MVP to<br>business in a week.</h2>
   362→    <p class="section-sub fade-up">Habitat Residency is not a course. Not a coworking space. Not another accelerator. It's one week where you only build.</p>
   363→
   364→    <div class="intro-grid fade-up">
   365→      <div class="intro-text">
   366→        <h3>The premise is simple.</h3>
   367→        <p>Five founders, already past idea stage, live and work together for seven consecutive days. No commute. No context-switching. No meetings except the ones that matter.</p>
   368→        <p>You get a dedicated mentor — a practitioner, not a professor — who works alongside you for the full week. You get access to a VC network for feedback and potential funding. And on day seven, you pitch.</p>
   369→        <p>The goal isn't to raise money that week (though it happens). The goal is to leave knowing exactly where you're going and why.</p>
   370→      </div>
   371→      <div class="intro-stats">
   372→        <div class="intro-stat">
   373→          <div class="intro-stat-num">5</div>
   374→          <div class="intro-stat-label">founders per cohort — small enough to build real trust</div>
   375→        </div>
   376→        <div class="intro-stat">
   377→          <div class="intro-stat-num">7</div>
   378→          <div class="intro-stat-label">consecutive days of focused, undistracted building</div>
   379→        </div>
   380→        <div class="intro-stat">
   381→          <div class="intro-stat-num">1</div>
   382→          <div class="intro-stat-label">dedicated mentor with you the entire week</div>
   383→        </div>
   384→        <div class="intro-stat">
   385→          <div class="intro-stat-num">0</div>
   386→          <div class="intro-stat-label">equity taken — ever</div>
   387→        </div>
   388→      </div>
   389→    </div>
   390→  </div>
   391→</section>
