   459→<!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
   460→<section style="background: var(--cream);">
   461→  <div class="container">
   462→    <div class="section-label fade-up">Who we select</div>
   463→    <h2 class="section-title fade-up">Already past zero.</h2>
   464→    <p class="section-sub fade-up">The Residency is for founders who've proven they can ship — and are ready to figure out whether they can build a business.</p>
   465→
   466→    <div class="criteria-grid">
   467→      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
   468→        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
   469→        <h3>You've shipped an MVP</h3>
   470→        <p>You have a live product — not a landing page, not a deck. Real code, real users, even if early. You know you can build.</p>
   471→      </div>
   472→      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
   473→        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
   474→        <h3>You're pre or early revenue</h3>
   475→        <p>You have some validation but you're not yet at scale. The Residency accelerates the period between "it works" and "it grows."</p>
   476→      </div>
   477→      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
   478→        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
   479→        <h3>You can be all-in for a week</h3>
   480→        <p>No day job meetings. No half-presence. Seven days of full focus. If you can't commit to that, the timing isn't right yet.</p>
   481→      </div>
   482→      <div class="criteria-card fade-up">
   483→        <div class="criteria-check">✓</div>
   484→        <h3>You want to be challenged</h3>
   485→        <p>The cohort and mentor will push you. Good feedback is uncomfortable. You need to want that, not just tolerate it.</p>
   486→      </div>
   487→    </div>
   488→  </div>
   489→</section>
